The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Saturday, January 31, 2004 				 Acid attack on Mumbai local train
 ANAND SOONDAS Mumbai, Jan. 30: Three  commuters were battling for life after wayside assailants  threw acid on them tonight in an unusual attack on Mumbais  lifeline.																								The passengers on the local train from Churchgate to Malad were targeted near Bandra in western Mumbai.																								Police said the train had just left Bandra station when the assailants struck from a slum along the tracks. They threw acid-filled polythene packs at a ladies compartment that had been made accessible to men. One of the ladies compartments is usually thrown open for all after 10 pm.																								The three passengers  Shirley Thomas, 25, Manasi Karnik, 30, and Prasanna, 28  have been rushed to hospital. Other passengers pulled the emergency chain and searched the slum but the assailants had fled by then.																								Incidents of stone-pelting at trains had been reported from the area but this is the first time that acid pouches are being used. 
